{"questionId":"4077","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>There is a proposal to power a space satellite X as it orbits the Earth. In this model,&nbsp;X is connected by an electronically-conducting cable to another smaller satellite Y.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/d7274f839241d314d3105b99ea8fc9ec01cddba9.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Satellite X orbits 6600 km from the centre of the Earth.</p>\n<p>Mass of the Earth = 6.0&nbsp;x 10<sup>24</sup> kg</p>\n<p>Show that the orbital speed of satellite X is about 8 km s<sup>–1</sup>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>«<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"v = \\sqrt {\\frac{{G{M_E}}}{r}} \">\n  <mi>v</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <msqrt>\n    <mfrac>\n      <mrow>\n        <mi>G</mi>\n        <mrow>\n          <msub>\n            <mi>M</mi>\n            <mi>E</mi>\n          </msub>\n        </mrow>\n      </mrow>\n      <mi>r</mi>\n    </mfrac>\n  </msqrt>\n</math></span>» = <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\sqrt {\\frac{{6.67 \\times {{10}^{ - 11}} \\times 6.0 \\times {{10}^{24}}}}{{6600 \\times {{10}^3}}}} \">\n  <msqrt>\n    <mfrac>\n      <mrow>\n        <mn>6.67</mn>\n        <mo>×</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <msup>\n            <mrow>\n              <mn>10</mn>\n            </mrow>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo>−</mo>\n              <mn>11</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </msup>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>×</mo>\n        <mn>6.0</mn>\n        <mo>×</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <msup>\n            <mrow>\n              <mn>10</mn>\n            </mrow>\n            <mrow>\n              <mn>24</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </msup>\n        </mrow>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mn>6600</mn>\n        <mo>×</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <msup>\n            <mrow>\n              <mn>10</mn>\n            </mrow>\n            <mn>3</mn>\n          </msup>\n        </mrow>\n      </mrow>\n    </mfrac>\n  </msqrt>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>7800 «m s<sup>–1</sup>»</p>\n<p><em>Full substitution required</em></p>\n<p><em>Must see 2+ significant figures.</em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"4077","referenceCode":"17N.2.HL.TZ0.2a","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Satellite X orbits 6600 km from the centre of the Earth. Mass of the Earth = 6.0 x 1024 kg Show that the orbital speed of satellite X is about 8 km s–1.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Additional higher level (AHL)","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 10: Fields","10.2 – Fields at work","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 10: Fields"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}